21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:32:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','local-search-optimization','','','2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:59:33','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/local-search-optimization/',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(73,0,'2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:32:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','social-media-marketing','','','2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:59:33','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/social-media-marketing/',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(74,0,'2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:32:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','google-ads-ppc','','','2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:59:33','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/google-ads-ppc/',9,'nav_menu_item','',0),(75,0,'2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:32:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','reputation-management','','','2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:59:33','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/reputation-management/',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(76,0,'2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:32:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','email-sms-campaigns','','','2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:59:33','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/email-sms-campaigns/',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(77,0,'2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:32:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','branding-logo-design','','','2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:59:33','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/branding-logo-design/',12,'nav_menu_item','',0),(78,0,'2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:32:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','b2b-commercial-lead-generation','','','2026-06-17 21:59:33','2026-06-17 21:59:33','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/b2b-commercial-lead-generation/',13,'nav_menu_item','',0),(79,1,'2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','<h2>The Challenge</h2>\n<p>Precision Air Flow, a family-owned HVAC company serving the greater metropolitan area, was struggling to stay afloat. They averaged 2-3 service calls per day during peak season, well below their break-even point of 6 calls daily. Their website was outdated, they had no Google Business Profile strategy, and their ad budget was being wasted on broad keywords like \"AC repair\" with no geo-targeting.</p>\n\n<h2>The Strategy</h2>\n<p>We implemented a three-pronged approach:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Local SEO Overhaul:</strong> Rebuilt their Google Business Profile with proper categories, service area mapping, and photo optimization. Built 12 location-specific landing pages targeting their primary service zones.</li>\n<li><strong>Targeted Google Ads:</strong> Narrowed keyword focus to emergency HVAC terms like \"furnace not working\" and \"AC not cooling\" with radius targeting of 15 miles. Implemented call-only ads for mobile users.</li>\n<li><strong>Review Generation System:</strong> Set up an automated review request sequence that turned every completed job into a potential 5-star review.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>The Results</h2>\n<div class=\"result-stats\">\n<div class=\"result-card\"><strong>300%</strong> increase in monthly calls</div>\n<div class=\"result-card\"><strong>180%</strong> revenue growth in 90 days</div>\n<div class=\"result-card\"><strong>4.9★</strong> average rating from 47 reviews</div>\n</div>\n<p>Within 90 days, Precision Air Flow was averaging 9+ calls per day. Their Google Business Profile ranked in the top 3 local pack for 14 high-value keywords. The ROI on their ad spend reached 8:1 by month three.</p>\n\n<h2>Client Testimonial</h2>\n<blockquote>\"We were about to close up shop. LeadZap turned everything around. I went from worrying about making payroll to turning down jobs because we are too busy. Best decision we ever made.\" - Mike R., Owner</blockquote>','Precision Air Flow: 3x Leads in 90 Days with HVAC SEO &amp; Google Ads','A small HVAC company went from 2 calls a day to 9+, boosting monthly revenue by 180% through targeted local SEO and Google Ads management.','publish','open','open','','precision-air-flow-hvac-case-study','','','2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/precision-air-flow-hvac-case-study/',0,'post','',0),(80,1,'2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','<h2>The Challenge</h2>\n<p>Summit Roofing Co had been in business for 8 years but was virtually invisible online. They ranked on page 4 of Google Maps for their primary keyword \"roofing contractor [city]\". Their Google Business Profile was unclaimed with incorrect hours, missing categories, and zero reviews. They were losing an estimated 15-20 qualified leads per week to competitors who dominated the local pack.</p>\n\n<h2>The Strategy</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>GBP Rescue:</strong> Claimed and verified their Google Business Profile. Corrected NAP consistency across 30+ directories. Added high-quality photos of completed roofing projects.</li>\n<li><strong>Citation Cleanup:</strong> Removed duplicate listings, corrected inconsistent business names and addresses across Yelp, BBB, HomeAdvisor, and industry directories.</li>\n<li><strong>Local Content:</strong> Created city-specific service pages for 8 surrounding towns, each with unique content about roofing services in that area.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>The Results</h2>\n<p>In just 6 weeks, Summit Roofing Co reached the #1 position in the local 3-pack for their primary keyword. Their monthly leads went from 3-5 to 25+. Revenue increased by 340%.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>#1</strong> Google Maps rank for primary keyword</li>\n<li><strong>340%</strong> increase in monthly leads</li>\n<li><strong>25+</strong> qualified calls per week</li>\n<li><strong>4.8★</strong> from 23 reviews in first quarter</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Client Testimonial</h2>\n<blockquote>\"I had no idea how much business I was leaving on the table. Being #1 on Google Maps changed everything for my company. The phone does not stop ringing.\" - Tom S., Owner</blockquote>','Summit Roofing Co: From Page 4 to #1 in Google Maps in 6 Weeks','A roofing contractor buried on page 4 of Google Maps achieved the #1 spot in their primary city in just 6 weeks through strategic local SEO.','publish','open','open','','summit-roofing-local-seo-case-study','','','2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/summit-roofing-local-seo-case-study/',0,'post','',0),(81,1,'2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','<h2>The Challenge</h2>\n<p>West Coast Electric was stuck in the residential service cycle: low-ticket repairs, high competition, and seasonal slowdowns. Their owner wanted to break into commercial contracting but had no pipeline for finding commercial projects. They were competing with dozens of other electricians for $150 service calls instead of going after $15,000+ commercial contracts.</p>\n\n<h2>The Strategy</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Permit Tracking:</strong> We set up daily monitoring of building permits, new construction filings, and commercial renovation applications across their target counties.</li>\n<li><strong>B2B Outreach:</strong> Created a targeted email sequence for property managers, general contractors, and facility directors. Each contact was enriched with phone numbers and company profiles.</li>\n<li><strong>Commercial Landing Page:</strong> Built a dedicated commercial services page highlighting their capabilities, insurance, certifications, and past commercial work.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>The Results</h2>\n<p>In just 60 days, West Coast Electric landed 3 commercial contracts worth a combined $48,000. Their average job value went from $180 (residential) to $16,000 (commercial).</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>$48k</strong> in commercial contracts secured</li>\n<li><strong>3</strong> new commercial clients in 60 days</li>\n<li><strong>89x</strong> increase in average job value</li>\n<li><strong>12</strong> active commercial leads in pipeline</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Client Testimonial</h2>\n<blockquote>\"I was tired of chasing $150 service calls. The B2B program from LeadZap opened a whole new revenue stream I did not know existed. These commercial contracts have completely changed my business.\" - Dave W., Owner</blockquote>','West Coast Electric: How B2B Lead Generation Landed 8k in Commercial Contracts','An electrical contractor shifted from residential service calls to high-value commercial contracts through B2B permit tracking and targeted outreach.','publish','open','open','','west-coast-electric-b2b-case-study','','','2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/west-coast-electric-b2b-case-study/',0,'post','',0),(82,1,'2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','<h2>The Challenge</h2>\n<p>FlowMaster Plumbing was spending $3,000 per month on Google Ads with poor results. Their campaigns were targeting broad keywords like \"plumber\" across a 50-mile radius, attracting unqualified clicks from outside their service area. Their cost per lead was over $120, and they could not trace which campaigns were actually generating calls.</p>\n\n<h2>The Strategy</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Keyword Restructuring:</strong> Narrowed focus to high-intent, emergency plumbing terms like \"emergency plumber near me\", \"burst pipe repair\", and \"water heater leaking\" with 10-mile radius targeting.</li>\n<li><strong>Call-Only Campaigns:</strong> Implemented call-only ads for mobile traffic, eliminating wasted clicks from users who just wanted information rather than service.</li>\n<li><strong>Negative Keywords:</strong> Added 200+ negative keywords to filter out DIY seekers, parts suppliers, and out-of-area searches.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>The Results</h2>\n<p>The campaign restructure delivered immediate results. Cost per lead dropped from $120 to just $18. Total monthly leads increased by 400% while ad spend actually decreased.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>12:1</strong> return on ad spend</li>\n<li><strong>60%</strong> reduction in cost per acquisition</li>\n<li><strong>400%</strong> increase in qualified leads</li>\n<li><strong>47</strong> calls per month from an $1,800 budget</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Client Testimonial</h2>\n<blockquote>\"I was about to give up on Google Ads entirely. LeadZap showed me I was doing it all wrong. Now my ad spend pays for itself 12 times over. The phone rings off the hook.\" - Carlos M., Owner</blockquote>','FlowMaster Plumbing: 12:1 ROAS with Precision Google Ads Campaign','A plumbing company was burning $3,000/month on Google Ads with almost no ROI. After a complete campaign restructure, they achieved 12:1 return on ad spend.','publish','open','open','','flowmaster-plumbing-google-ads-case-study','','','2026-06-17 23:08:56','2026-06-17 23:08:56','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/flowmaster-plumbing-google-ads-case-study/',0,'post','',0),(83,1,'2026-06-18 04:50:39','2026-06-18 04:50:39','{\"version\": 3, \"isGlobalStylesUserThemeJSON\": true }','Custom Styles','','publish','closed','closed','','wp-global-styles-nimo','','','2026-06-18 04:50:39','2026-06-18 04:50:39','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/wp-global-styles-nimo/',0,'wp_global_styles','',0),(84,1,'2026-06-18 04:58:55','2026-06-18 04:58:55','','HVAC Lead Gen','','inherit','open','closed','','hvac-lead-gen','','','2026-06-18 04:58:55','2026-06-18 04:58:55','',0,'https://nimo-clone.87.106.124.206.nip.io/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/HVAC-Lead-Gen.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(85,0,'2026-06-18 05:05:37','2026-06-18 05:05:37','','port1.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','port1-jpg','','','2026-06-18 05:05:37','2026-06-18 05:05:37','',79,'/var/www/html/wp-content/themes/nimo/img/leadzap/port1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(86,0,'2026-06-18 05:05:37','2026-06-18 05:05:37','','port2.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','port2-jpg','','','2026-06-18 05:05:37','2026-06-18 05:05:37','',80,'/var/www/html/wp-content/themes/nimo/img/leadzap/port2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(87,0,'2026-06-18 05:05:37','2026-06-